cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with enhancing the visibility of rain videos through rain removal. The use of deep learning and convolutional neural networks also suggests that it may belong to the machine learning (cs.MM) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The establishment of a large-scale video database and the observation of temporal correlation and similar patterns of rain across video frames may also suggest that it could belong to the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category.
